r footfalls. Sometimes I think our love is inexperienced. The question of dying becomes a wise reminder. It cures us of our innocence of the future. Simple things are doomed, or is that a superstition? We watched the girls come round again. They were stru
ng out now, with faces and particular gaits, almost weightless in their craving, able to land lightly.
