\par Babette said, "Did you get the impression they were only making a suggestion or was it a little more mandatory, do you think?"
\par "It was a fire captain's car with a loudspeaker and it was going pretty fast."
\par I said, "In other words you didn't have an opportunity to notice the subtle edges of intonation."
\par "The voice was screaming out."
\par "Due to the sirens," Babette said helpfully.
